<br>
<br>
<a style="color: red;" href="https://kodi.tv/download/">So go ahead and click here to download Kodi </a>
<br>
<br>
<p>Make sure you choose the correct operating system for windows you use the windows one. I KNOW SHOCKING RIGHT Follow the prompts like you would for normal installation
So its installed</p>
<br>
<br>
<p>now open kodi it looks a bit bare right trust me its for the best</p>
<br>
<br>
<p>
now using the arrow keys go to the right to system don't click, Underneath you will see file manager go ahead and click that. On the next screen click the bottom option add source</p>
<br>
<br>
<h1 style="color: blue;"> oooh a box popped up</h1>
<br>
<br>
<p>go right ahead and type this into the top box exactly as it is here</p>
<br>
<br>
<h1 style="color: red;">http://fusion.tvaddons.ag</h1>
<br>
<br>
<p>
in the bottom box type in fusion then click ok at the bottom
Oh its getting going now its not so hard right
Now go back to the home screen using the backspace or return key or you can click the option .... at the top.</p>
<br>
<br>
<p>
Now you are back to where you selected file manager to the immediate left of file manager it says settings go ahead and click that! then click these options as they appear on the screen</p>
<br>
<br>
<p>
addons
install from zip
a side menu will pop up on the right select fusion
then click start here
then click plugin.program.addoninstaller-1.2.9.zip</p>
<br>
<br>
<p>
now after a few seconds you should get a notification in the bottom right hand side that says install complete!</p>
<br>
<br>
<h1 style="color: purple;"> oh coool you just installed an addon!</h1>
<br>
<br>
<p>
now go back to the addons menu if you cant remember how to get there it says it above
now click my addons
then program addons
then click addon installer then hit launch!
Now it will do a loading screen. We are almost done hang in there!
once it has loaded up you will be on a screen with green tiles
click featured addons now we gonna get your streamping addons loaded up</p>
<br>
<br>
<p>
exodus
<br>
phoenix
<br>
navi-x
<br>
stream all the sources (salts)
</p>
<br>

<p>these four are my preffered addons stable nice and easy to use, navi x takes some getting used to but it works a treat
now click exodus then click exodus again a menu will pop up asking you to confirm the install click yes wait fot the install to finish go back and download the rest!</p>
<br>
<b>
<h1 style="color: green;"> you have all the video addons now wooohooooo</h1>

<br>
<p>
Now you have them installed but they don't show up on home screen. Lets fix that!
so from the kodi home screen (where it has video music tv etc
Scroll to the right where it says system underneath click settings
then hit appearence now this bit takes a bit of notice once you hit appearence on the right hand side there is an option to click settings directly under the skin skin option</p>
<br>
<br>
<p>
click the settings then on the left select home window options
Now when you click on the right hand side a little blue dot will appear on the far right you want to make sure a blue dot is on for the following
</p>
<br>
<br>
<p>
weather
music
pictures
</p>
<br>
<br>
<p>
then on the left hand side click add-on shortcuts
Now where it says home page "videos" sub menu click add-on 1
then select an addon you installed earlier i usually have phoenix here because its my favourite do the same untill you run out of add-ons
</p>
<br>
<br>
<p>
then scroll down the page untill you find home page "program" shortcuts
select the first one and hit addon installer. Its like an app installer handy to have!
